news.title: Rapid urbanisation has left Mohali towns in civic mess
news.para: Mohali, Derabassi and Kharar share issues like illegal and haphazard construction, traffic and parking problem, broken roads, blocked sewerage, poor drainage, and lawlessness.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: Development buzz drives rental boom
news.para: Brokers in the city said flats in Yendada, Sagarnagar, Madhurawada, and PM Palem are now high in demand as the buzz is that development will be centred between Yendada and Madhurawada, till Anandapuram and Bheemili.

news.title: Should you buy Shriram Properties after a flop debut?
news.para: The scrip was listed at Rs 90 on the National Stock Exchange, a discount of 24 per cent over its issue price of Rs 118.

news.title: Hubballi: Property tax hiked by up to 800%, industry to intensity stir
news.para: While an Ilkal-based organisation has already filed a public interest litigation in the high court, several other organisations, including the Karnatak Chamber of Commerce and Industry, have formed an action committee to oppose the exorbitant hike.

news.title: Mysuru civic body to open B register to increase tax revenue
news.para: According to MCC officials, there are 1.92 lakh properties under the corporation limits. MCC has property tax arrears of around Rs 92 crore for the 2020-2021 financial year. MCC had set a target of Rs 140 crore property tax collection for 2021-22.

news.title: Shriram Properties shares list with nearly 24% discount
news.para: ​The stock listed at Rs 94, a decline of 20.33 per cent from the issue price on the BSE. It further tumbled 22.24 per cent to Rs 91.75.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to probe Rs 50 crore C&D waste fraud by private firm
news.para: Officials said the probe panel was formed by commissioner Mukesh Kumar Ahuja following directions from the urban local bodies department.

news.title: China's Kaisa says bondholders have not asked for accelerated repayments yet
news.para: Kaisa Group said it also did not pay the coupon totalling $105 million for notes due in 2023, 2025, and 2026, with the grace period for the first two already expired.

news.title: Odisha completes construction of over 31 lakh homes under rural housing schemes
news.para: As many as 31,08,471 houses allotted to beneficiaries under different schemes were completed, and 1,75,960 houses were in different stages of construction, the official said.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government to construct 960 homes for housing board flat owners
news.para: After a meeting with owners of Singanallur housing board flat owners in the city on Sunday, Muthusamy told reporters that the new apartments would be more spacious, stronger and better than the existing one.

news.title: WeWork India looks to add 1 million sq ft coworking space in 2022
news.para: WeWork continues to remain bullish and focus on the growth of flexible workspaces in the country and has closed some large deals running between 200,000 and 300,000 square feet, the India CEO said.

news.title: Gurugram: Pyramid Urban Homes residents say builder yet to build 33 kV infra
news.para: The developer, they claimed, is yet to build a 33 kV switching station despite collecting an average of Rs 50,000 per flat as electricity infrastructure development charges. The result is two-three hours of power cuts daily.

news.title: China's property distress sours steel sector in warning sign for economy
news.para: The spreading balance-sheet crisis at real estate firms is a warning for policymakers as a swing in the fortunes of the steel industry would have significant repercussions for China's economy, with cement, glass, and household appliances all vulnerable to demand drops.

news.title: Railway department to monetise land on Kalka-Shimla section
news.para: The RLDA team made measurements and mapped the vacant land at various railway stations on the section. It will also outsource tea selling at all stations on the section.

news.title: Gurugram development body gets lukewarm response to feedback facility
news.para: “We have an open consultation facility on our website for people to share their perspectives, but they are not using it as much as we expected. We have been trying to make it interactive to encourage more people to participate,” said GMDA official.
